TO HIS MOST SERENE HIGHNESS THE KING. ARGUMENT.

While with the diadem of the sons of Fergus you touch the stars and sway the sceptre of your sires with a steady hand, it is uncertain whether you are to Britons Charles the First or Charles the Great, or both. Chanes the First you are, and by your deserved praises you so shine from the North as to be the Cynosure of your age.
